      "side": 1,
      "message": "The paths are like this:\n\n1. Both: eglCreateWindowSurface/eglCreatePbufferSurface from the guest call rcCreateWindowSurface, which calls eglCreatePbufferSurface, so anything the guest writes is a pbuffer\n2. eglCreateWindowSurface is only for the host\u0027s posting surface (subwindow), so we just get one per display\n\nIn the case where newDrawPtr/newReadPtr are not pbuffers, then it\u0027s the host\u0027s posting surface, and we are in a host-side posting routine. We don\u0027t want to emulate them since at this point, something actually needs to show up on screen (use FBO 0).",
